# Co-Op Growth Stages — Solo Developer Edition

> Replaces the old Phase 0-4 enterprise approach.
> See `docs/archive/2026-03-27_CO_OP_SOLO_DEVELOPER_ARCHITECTURE.md` for historical context.
> Current architecture documented in `.kiro/steering/architecture.md`

## The 4 Growth Stages

```
STAGE 1 (Week 1):     6 services — Company GPT. Talking chatbot.
STAGE 2 (Month 2):    8 services — Real AI. Telegram. Lead Search.
STAGE 3 (Month 3-4): 12 services — Agents proposing and communicating.
STAGE 4 (Month 5+):  Full v5.3 — When revenue justifies complexity.
```

**The One Rule:** Never add a service unless you feel the pain of not having it.

---

## Stage 1 — The Foundation

**Services:** co-op-api, co-op-web, postgres, redis, qdrant, minio
**Goal:** Working chatbot you can demo to anyone
**Deliverables:**
- Upload PDF → AI answers questions (RAG pipeline)
- Login, dashboard, search, chat all work
- v0.1.0 on GitHub

**Not yet:** Real LLM, Telegram, agents, external APIs

---

## Stage 2 — Real Intelligence

**Add:** ollama (+11434), litellm (+4000)
**Goal:** Real LLM + Telegram control + Upwork reading
**Key decisions:**
- **ARQ** for background tasks (not Celery)
- Telegram bot runs **inside co-op-api** (no new container)
- Lead Scout uses **httpx** (no Browserless yet)

**Deliverables:**
- Real LLM-generated answers
- Telegram: /status, /pause, /panic, /approve, /budget
- Lead Scout reading Upwork every 4 hours
- Morning brief at 8am
- Hardware detection + sandbox tier

---

## Stage 3 — Working Agents

**Add:** browserless (+8030), vault (+8200), llm-guard (+8060), communication (+8010)
**Goal:** Proposals submitted. First revenue.
**Architecture notes:**
- STILL no Temporal — use ARQ task chains
- STILL no NATS — Redis queues are fine
- STILL no Neo4j — PostgreSQL JSONB
- STILL no OPA — FastAPI role checks
- STILL no microsandbox — Docker sandbox only

**Deliverables:**
- Proposal Writer automates proposals
- HITL approval via Telegram
- Outreach Manager submits to Upwork
- Client Communicator handles email
- Project Tracker with milestones
- Finance Manager creates invoices
- Simulation mode for testing

---

## Stage 4 — Scaling to Full v5.3

**Add:** only when you feel the specific pain (see trigger list)
**Goal:** Enterprise-grade components as needed

**Key triggers:**
| Pain | Add |
|------|-----|
| ARQ loses tasks on crash | Temporal |
| Agents burn money in loops | Zombie detector |
| Need to debug agent decisions | OpenTelemetry + Grafana |
| Docker sandbox feels unsafe | microsandbox |
| Complex permissions for team | OPA |
| 50+ clients need graph queries | Neo4j |
| Revenue > £10k, need scale | Traefik + multi-node |

See `docs/stages/phase-3/stage4_implementation.md` for full trigger list.

